WEBVTT

00:14.848 --> 00:16.617
[SCREECHING]

00:16.684 --> 00:17.718
[SCREECHING]

00:17.785 --> 00:19.420
HUH?

00:19.487 --> 00:21.389
[WIND WHOOSHING]

00:21.455 --> 00:23.557
WHOA!

00:31.799 --> 00:33.601
[SCREECHING]

00:34.635 --> 00:37.271
AAAAAHHH!

00:40.274 --> 00:41.375
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:41.442 --> 00:42.943
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

00:43.010 --> 00:46.013
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

00:46.080 --> 00:47.248
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

00:47.315 --> 00:49.117
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

00:49.183 --> 00:52.120
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:52.186 --> 00:53.221
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

00:53.287 --> 00:54.622
* WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW YOU *

00:54.688 --> 00:57.858
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

00:57.925 --> 00:59.260
* WE SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

00:59.327 --> 01:00.594
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:00.661 --> 01:04.064
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:05.333 --> 01:07.067
* DON'T LOOK BACK *

01:07.135 --> 01:09.603
* YOU MAY FIND
ANOTHER CLUE *

01:11.372 --> 01:15.409
* SCOOBY SNAX WILL BE
WAITING HERE FOR YOU *

01:15.476 --> 01:17.111
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:17.178 --> 01:18.512
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:18.579 --> 01:21.549
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:21.615 --> 01:22.983
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:23.050 --> 01:24.518
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:24.585 --> 01:27.188
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:27.255 --> 01:28.922
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:28.989 --> 01:30.424
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:30.491 --> 01:33.427
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

01:33.494 --> 01:36.430
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:36.497 --> 01:39.367
* WHAT'S NEW,
SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:45.839 --> 01:47.375
MAN, THOSE
NEW MEXICO SKIES

01:47.441 --> 01:50.844
ARE A FEAST
FOR THE EYES.

01:50.911 --> 01:54.182
LIKE, IT'S TOO BAD
MY EYES AREN'T THE PART
THAT'S HUNGRY.

01:54.248 --> 01:56.116
WE'RE ALMOST
TO SANTA FE, SHAGGY.

01:56.184 --> 01:59.387
YOU CAN GET A SNACK
AFTER WE DROP OFF
YOUR STATUE AT THE GALLERY.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.322
IT'S REALLY GREAT
SHAGGY'S SCOOBY
SCULPTURE

02:01.389 --> 02:02.656
WAS ENTERED
IN THAT ART SHOW.

02:02.723 --> 02:06.126
I OWE IT ALL
TO THE PERFECT
SCULPTURE MODEL.

02:07.528 --> 02:08.529
[LAUGHTER]

02:09.597 --> 02:10.598
BEEP BEEP!

02:15.636 --> 02:16.270
"MEEP MEEP"?

02:16.337 --> 02:17.905
"COCHITI RESERVATION."

02:17.971 --> 02:20.408
HEY, JIMMY PROUDWOLF
LIVES THERE.

02:20.474 --> 02:22.510
WE'VE BEEN PALS
SINCE WE WERE LITTLE KIDS.

02:22.576 --> 02:25.246
I'D SURE LOVE HIM TO SEE
MY SCOOBY SCULPTURE.

02:25.313 --> 02:27.147
YEAH. ME, TOO.

02:27.215 --> 02:28.416
WELL, I THINK
WE HAVE TIME

02:28.482 --> 02:30.584
FOR A LITTLE
LUNCH DETOUR.

02:30.651 --> 02:33.421
WHOA!
WHOA!

02:35.223 --> 02:37.525
HANG ON!

02:37.591 --> 02:39.393
THANKS FOR
THE WARNING,
FREDDY.

02:43.231 --> 02:45.466
Velma: "LIKE, JIMMY'S
DREAMCATCHERS."

02:48.769 --> 02:49.703
LIKE, JIMMY!

02:49.770 --> 02:51.772
LIKE, SHAGGY!

02:56.410 --> 02:58.078
HA HA HA HA.
HA HA HA HA.

02:58.145 --> 03:00.981
JIMMY PROUDWOLF,
THIS IS VELMA,
DAPHNE, AND FRED.

03:01.048 --> 03:02.250
HELLO.
HI, THERE.

03:02.316 --> 03:04.252
AND YOU
REMEMBER SCOOBY.

03:04.318 --> 03:06.720
NO WAY!
CHECK OUT SHOOBY!

03:06.787 --> 03:07.921
NO WAY!

03:07.988 --> 03:10.758
LIKE, MAYBE WE
BETTER GET INSIDE.

03:10.824 --> 03:12.626
[THUNDER]

03:14.262 --> 03:16.230
UH, EXPECTING RAIN?

03:16.297 --> 03:18.432
IF IT WERE ONLY THAT.

03:21.101 --> 03:23.271
BAA.
BAA.
BAA.

03:35.249 --> 03:37.451
BAA.
BAA.
BAA.

03:39.820 --> 03:43.190
THIS STATUE OF SCOOBY
IS FOR A SCULPTURE SHOW
IN SANTA FE.

03:43.257 --> 03:46.226
NO WAY. I'M KIND OF
AN ARTIST NOW, TOO.

03:46.294 --> 03:48.862
I MAKE DREAM CATCHERS
AND SELL THEM TO ANYONE

03:48.929 --> 03:50.898
WHO SHARES THEIR VIBES.

03:50.964 --> 03:52.700
NO WAY!

03:58.238 --> 03:59.440
[GULP]
[GULP]

03:59.507 --> 04:01.675
YOU TWO ARE LIKE
2 SOYBEANS IN A POD.

04:01.742 --> 04:02.810
HA HA HA HA.

04:02.876 --> 04:04.378
LIKE, WE'VE
BEEN BUDDIES
SINCE WE MET

04:04.445 --> 04:06.480
AT THE REDWOOD
RABBIT DAYCARE
CENTER.

04:06.547 --> 04:08.616
JIMMY TIED ME
FOR MOST GOLD
STICKERS

04:08.682 --> 04:09.783
IN NAPTIME.

04:09.850 --> 04:11.785
BUT SHAGGY WAS
THE ALL-STICKER
CHAMPION

04:11.852 --> 04:12.920
IN SNACKTIME.

04:12.986 --> 04:14.021
NO WAY!

04:14.087 --> 04:15.556
UH, COMING UP HERE,

04:15.623 --> 04:17.825
LIKE, YOU DIDN'T NOTICE
ANYTHING UNUSUAL

04:17.891 --> 04:19.360
IN THE SKIES, DID YOU?

04:19.427 --> 04:22.296
JUST THE BEAUTIFUL
NEW MEXICO CLOUD FORMATIONS.

04:22.363 --> 04:24.798
THERE WAS ONE SHAPED
LIKE BOXER SHORTS.

04:24.865 --> 04:28.201
MAYBE WE SHOULD
GET SCOOBY AND SHOOBY
INSIDE, TOO.

04:28.268 --> 04:30.237
BUT WHY?
THEY SEEM
TO BE HAVING

04:30.304 --> 04:32.373
SO MUCH FUN UP
ON THAT HILLSIDE.

04:34.375 --> 04:36.009
[SCREECHING]

04:36.076 --> 04:38.045
HUH?
THAT'S WHY!

04:40.147 --> 04:42.850
[SCREECHING]

04:42.916 --> 04:44.885
HUH? HUH?

04:44.952 --> 04:45.986
ROH!

04:47.588 --> 04:49.457
Fred: RUN,
SCOOBY! RUN!

04:49.523 --> 04:52.360
Shaggy: HEY, YOU BIG BIRD,
LEAVE HIM ALONE!

04:52.426 --> 04:53.727
[SCREECHING]

04:59.400 --> 05:00.834
[SCREECHING]

05:00.901 --> 05:02.536
WHOA!

05:03.404 --> 05:04.805
Velma: LET ME GUESS.

05:04.872 --> 05:07.741
THAT WAS
THE UNUSUAL THING
IN THE SKY?

05:07.808 --> 05:09.076
I THOUGHT
SEEING BOXER SHORTS

05:09.142 --> 05:10.578
WAS STRANGE.

05:10.644 --> 05:12.713
THAT FEATHERED FIEND
SNATCHED SHAGGY'S SCULPTURE

05:12.780 --> 05:13.847
OF SCOOBY!

05:13.914 --> 05:15.716
BETTER THAN SNATCHING
THE REAL THING.

05:15.783 --> 05:17.518
YOU SAID IT.

05:20.654 --> 05:23.190
EXCUSE ME.
HAVE YOU SEEN
A GIANT, VICIOUS

05:23.256 --> 05:24.358
HOOK-CLAWED BIRDY?

05:24.425 --> 05:25.593
ONLY ONE TODAY.

05:25.659 --> 05:27.961
OH! WHERE?
WHERE? WHERE?!

05:28.028 --> 05:29.730
IT FLEW AWAY.

05:29.797 --> 05:31.231
OH...CHIRP!

05:31.298 --> 05:33.467
Fred: AND YOU ARE?

05:33.534 --> 05:36.504
HI. I'M AVERY ORENTHALL,
LIFELONG BIRD WATCHER.

05:36.570 --> 05:38.706
SEEN EVERY RARE
NORTH AMERICAN BIRD.

05:38.772 --> 05:40.140
CHECKED THEM OFF
THIS CARD.

05:40.207 --> 05:42.610
EVEN THE SPINE-BILLED
DICKEY GREBE!

05:42.676 --> 05:44.912
NOW, I'VE HEARD ABOUT
THIS FOUL-FEATHERED FOWL

05:44.978 --> 05:46.814
NEVER YET WATCHED
BY ANY BIRD WATCHER,

05:46.880 --> 05:49.917
AND I'M GOING TO BE
THE WATCHER
WHO WATCHES IT.

05:49.983 --> 05:50.984
I GOTTA FLY!

05:53.220 --> 05:55.589
SO, JIMMY, MAYBE
NOW'S A GOOD TIME

05:55.656 --> 05:57.858
TO TELL US WHAT'S
GOING ON AROUND HERE.

05:57.925 --> 05:59.026
LIKE, I WISH I KNEW.

05:59.092 --> 06:01.529
THAT'S THING'S APPEARED
A FEW TIMES LATELY.

06:01.595 --> 06:03.531
JUST YESTERDAY A MAN
FROM THE RESERVATION

06:03.597 --> 06:05.833
WAS EXPLORING
ON THE MOUNTAIN, AND...

06:05.899 --> 06:07.367
IT CARRIED HIM AWAY!

06:07.435 --> 06:08.936
HOW HORRIBLE!

06:09.002 --> 06:11.371
YEAH. MY PEOPLE
ARE REALLY BUMMED.

06:11.439 --> 06:12.906
THEY'VE CALLED FOR
A TRAVELING SHAMAN

06:12.973 --> 06:15.308
TO SPEAK TO US TONIGHT
IN THE SWEAT LODGE.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.777
HE SPEAKS
WHILE YOU SWEAT?

06:16.844 --> 06:20.681
IT'S WHERE WE GO
TO SEARCH FOR
THE BIG ANSWERS.

06:20.748 --> 06:23.083
SEARCHING FOR ANSWERS
IS RIGHT UP OUR ALLEY.

06:23.150 --> 06:25.453
WOULD YOU MIND
IF WE JOINED YOU
IN THE SWEAT LODGE?

06:25.519 --> 06:27.387
SURE. EVERYONE'S
WELCOME.

06:27.455 --> 06:29.356
YOU'LL GET TO LEARN
ABOUT OUR PROBLEM.

06:29.423 --> 06:30.558
I'LL ALSO GET
TO MAKE UP

06:30.624 --> 06:32.693
FOR MISSING
MY SPA SESSION.

06:37.898 --> 06:41.502
THE ANASAZI PEOPLE
WHO MADE THEIR HOMES

06:41.569 --> 06:43.537
IN THE CAVES
ABOVE YOUR VILLAGE--

06:43.604 --> 06:47.508
THEY ALL DISAPPEARED
1,300 YEARS AGO.

06:47.575 --> 06:50.711
NOBODY KNOWS
WHERE THEY WENT.

06:52.580 --> 06:55.983
WOW. NOW, THEY
REALLY HAD A MYSTERY
ON THEIR HANDS.

06:56.049 --> 06:57.050
SHH!

06:57.117 --> 06:58.085
OKAY.

06:58.151 --> 06:59.487
IN THEIR CAVES

06:59.553 --> 07:02.556
WE FIND THE PICTOGRAPHS,
THE WALL PAINTINGS.

07:02.623 --> 07:05.626
THEY SHOW A GIGANTIC
FLYING BEAST.

07:05.693 --> 07:08.729
IT IS THE WAKUMI!

07:08.796 --> 07:12.032
IT IS A DREADFUL SPIRIT
FROM ANASAZI LEGEND.

07:12.099 --> 07:15.435
IT DID NOT WANT INTRUDERS
CLIMBING UP THE MOUNTAIN

07:15.503 --> 07:18.071
TO THE SACRED
HUNTING GROUNDS
OF THE GODS.

07:19.072 --> 07:21.308
[WHIMPERING]

07:21.374 --> 07:22.776
[ALL GASP]

07:24.277 --> 07:26.547
DID IT SCARE AWAY
THE ANASAZI?

07:26.614 --> 07:28.749
WE WILL NEVER KNOW
THE ANSWER.

07:28.816 --> 07:31.819
HAS THE WAKUMI RETURNED
FOR YOUR PEOPLE?

07:31.885 --> 07:35.255
YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW
THE HORROR.

07:35.322 --> 07:36.757
[WHIMPERING]

07:46.433 --> 07:49.036
[SCREECHING]

07:49.102 --> 07:50.237
JEEPERS!
JINKIES!

07:55.342 --> 07:57.911
[SCREECHING]

07:57.978 --> 07:59.880
WHOA!
AAH!

07:59.947 --> 08:01.481
WHOA! UNH!

08:12.425 --> 08:14.995
WHAT WE NEED IS
A 500-POUND CAT.

08:15.062 --> 08:18.065
SORRY ABOUT YOUR POOR,
BROKEN SCULPTURE, SHAGGY.

08:18.131 --> 08:21.635
NO PROBLEM.
SCOOB WILL JUST POSE
FOR ANOTHER ONE.

08:27.474 --> 08:29.176
I HEARD THE COMMOTION.

08:31.411 --> 08:33.747
HAVE YOU SEEN A GREAT,
GLIDING GRABBER?

08:33.814 --> 08:35.282
I CAME UP
WITH THAT NAME MYSELF.

08:35.348 --> 08:36.349
YOU MISSED IT AGAIN.

08:36.416 --> 08:37.818
IT FLEW UP
TO THAT MOUNTAIN.

08:37.885 --> 08:40.888
OHHH...CHIRP AND TWEET!

08:41.889 --> 08:43.323
STRANGE HOW
THAT BIRD WATCHER

08:43.390 --> 08:45.425
ALWAYS SEEMS TO BE
MISSING HIS BIRD.

08:45.492 --> 08:47.561
IS THAT WHERE
THE CLIFF DWELLINGS ARE?

08:47.628 --> 08:48.596
Jimmy: YEAH, MAN.

08:48.662 --> 08:50.197
THE ANASAZI
LIVED IN THE CAVES

08:50.263 --> 08:51.665
ABOVE THE RESERVATION.

08:51.732 --> 08:54.635
AND THE MOUNTAIN CONTINUES
A MILE BEYOND THAT.

08:54.702 --> 08:56.637
CAN YOU AND SHOOBY
TAKE US UP THERE, JIMMY?

08:56.704 --> 08:59.039
UH, WE'RE KINDA SCARED
OF HEIGHTS.

08:59.106 --> 09:01.041
BUT, LIKE,
THERE'S THIS GIRL
ON THE RESERVATION

09:01.108 --> 09:03.644
WHO'S A TOTAL EXPERT--
CODY LONG.

09:03.711 --> 09:05.913
SHE'LL HELP YOU SCALE
ANY DIZZYING, SLIPPERY,

09:05.979 --> 09:08.248
SHEER-DROP,
MILE-HIGH MOUNTAIN.

09:10.017 --> 09:12.119
CAREFUL.
THOSE LADDERS
HAVE BEEN HERE

09:12.185 --> 09:13.921
FOR HUNDREDS
OF YEARS.

09:15.455 --> 09:17.825
TOO BAD THEY DIDN'T
HAVE ESCALATORS.

09:17.891 --> 09:18.892
MM-HMM.

09:21.061 --> 09:22.896
THANKS, CODY.

09:24.832 --> 09:25.799
WOW.

09:29.136 --> 09:32.339
THOSE MUST BE THE PICTURES
THE SHAMAN WAS TALKING ABOUT.

09:32.405 --> 09:33.874
Cody: THEY'RE CALLED
PICTOGRAPHS.

09:33.941 --> 09:36.276
THEY TELL THE STORIES
OF THE PEOPLE'S LIVES,

09:36.343 --> 09:38.278
WARS, HUNTS,
AND LEGENDS.

09:38.345 --> 09:41.114
HMM...THERE
DOESN'T SEEM TO BE
A PICTOGRAPH

09:41.181 --> 09:42.916
OF A BIG
WAKUMI BIRD.

09:45.318 --> 09:47.187
UHH--UHH!

09:47.254 --> 09:50.190
OH...WHOA! WHOA!

09:56.063 --> 09:56.997
AH-CHOO!

09:57.064 --> 09:58.298
WHOA!

10:02.569 --> 10:04.071
WHAT A PRETTY
FEATHER.

10:04.137 --> 10:06.106
I WONDER
WHAT KIND OF BIRD
IT BELONGED TO.

10:06.173 --> 10:09.142
I'D SAY IT CAME FROM
SOME SORT OF HAWK.

10:09.209 --> 10:10.177
A HAWK FEATHER?

10:10.243 --> 10:12.045
THAT COULD BE CONSIDERED
AN EVIL OMEN.

10:12.112 --> 10:14.547
IT COULD ALSO
BE CONSIDERED
A CLUE.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.316
WHAT'S RIGHT ABOVE
THESE CAVES?

10:16.383 --> 10:17.617
THE UPPER MESAS.

10:17.685 --> 10:19.286
FLATLANDS WHERE
THE ANASAZI FARMED

10:19.352 --> 10:20.721
FAR ABOVE THEIR ENEMIES.

10:20.788 --> 10:22.856
COULD YOU LEAD US
UP HIGHER, CODY,

10:22.923 --> 10:24.892
WHERE THE OLD ANASAZI
HAD A FARM?

10:24.958 --> 10:27.027
* EE-I-EE-I-OH *
* EE-I-EE-I-OH *

10:27.094 --> 10:30.363
HEE HEE HEE HEE.
HA HA HA HA.

10:30.430 --> 10:31.799
Shaggy: WELL,
OF ALL THE CREEPY,

10:31.865 --> 10:33.466
GHOSTLY PLACES
WE'VE EVER BEEN,

10:33.533 --> 10:37.004
THIS IS DEFINITELY
THE HIGHEST CREEPY,
GHOSTLY PLACE.

10:37.070 --> 10:38.839
Daphne: WHAT'S
ON THAT LEDGE UP THERE?

10:38.906 --> 10:40.140
SOMETHING SHINING.

10:40.207 --> 10:41.975
LET'S CLIMB UP THERE
AND CHECK IT OUT.

10:42.042 --> 10:44.745
WE'RE ALREADY HIGHER
THAN I'M SUPPOSED
TO TAKE YOU.

10:44.812 --> 10:45.879
OH, THAT'S OKAY.

10:45.946 --> 10:48.816
I CAN GET UP THERE
BY MYSELF.

10:48.882 --> 10:50.483
SHE SHOULDN'T GO
UP TO THAT LEDGE.

10:50.550 --> 10:53.520
IT'S NOT SAFE WITH
THAT TERRIBLE CREATURE
FLYING AROUND.

10:53.586 --> 10:55.355
BUT WE'RE GONNA
FIND OUT WHAT IT IS.

10:55.422 --> 10:58.191
[DAPHNE GASPS]
THIS IS WEIRD.

10:58.258 --> 10:59.226
HEADS UP!

11:01.328 --> 11:02.696
AN OXYGEN TANK.

11:02.763 --> 11:04.765
WHY WOULD THAT
BE UP HERE?

11:04.832 --> 11:06.233
HMM.
[SCREECH]

11:06.299 --> 11:07.968
DAPHNE, LOOK OUT!

11:08.501 --> 11:10.170
AAH!

11:10.237 --> 11:11.338
[SCREECHING]

11:11.404 --> 11:12.840
AAH! AAH!

11:12.906 --> 11:15.142
YIKES!
IT'S GOT HER!

11:16.977 --> 11:18.746
Cody: IT'S HEADING
FOR THOSE PEAKS.

11:18.812 --> 11:20.447
WE'VE GOT TO
SAVE DAPHNE.

11:20.513 --> 11:23.116
I CAN'T LEAD YOU UP
WHERE THE EVIL SPIRITS
REIGN.

11:23.183 --> 11:25.786
SHE SURE DOESN'T
SEEM TO WANT US
ON THAT MOUNTAIN.

11:25.853 --> 11:26.954
THEN I'LL TAKE US UP.

11:27.020 --> 11:29.056
I USED TO HIKE A LITTLE
IN YOSEMITE...

11:29.122 --> 11:31.892
TILL THE BEAR
TOOK MY CLOTHES.

11:31.959 --> 11:35.028
Velma: THE GUIDE BOOK SAID
THE TOP OF THIS MOUNTAIN
IS WHEELER PEAK,

11:35.095 --> 11:37.965
THE VERY HIGHEST POINT
IN NEW MEXICO.

11:38.031 --> 11:39.699
THINK CLIMBING, GUYS.

11:39.767 --> 11:41.034
Velma: WHEN YOU'RE
HUNDREDS OF FEET UP

11:41.101 --> 11:42.936
ON THE SHEER FACE
OF A MOUNTAIN WALL,

11:43.003 --> 11:44.938
THERE'S NOTHING ELSE
TO THINK ABOUT.

11:45.005 --> 11:46.774
EXCEPT, MAYBE, LUNCH?

11:46.840 --> 11:48.375
GOT YOU COVERED, SHAGGY.

11:48.441 --> 11:50.310
FREEZE DRIED
SCOOBY SNAX.

11:50.377 --> 11:51.511
JUST SWALLOW.

11:51.578 --> 11:53.847
SOUNDS LIKE REGULAR
SCOOBY SNAX.

11:55.615 --> 11:57.650
TRY SOME, SCOOB.

11:57.717 --> 11:58.952
BAAAA.

12:02.255 --> 12:04.091
Velma: THE AIR UP HERE
IS GETTING THIN.

12:04.157 --> 12:06.593
WE MIGHT START FEELING
LIGHT-HEADED.

12:06.659 --> 12:08.095
MAYBE THAT'S
WHY I'M SEEING

12:08.161 --> 12:10.530
A MOUNTAIN MADE
OF PEANUT BUTTER.

12:10.597 --> 12:12.565
[SCOOBY MUTTERS]

12:12.632 --> 12:15.903
Voice: TURN BACK. TURN BACK!

12:15.969 --> 12:18.772
NOW I HEAR SOMEBODY
SAYING, "TURN BACK."

12:18.839 --> 12:21.741
TURN BACK.
TURN BACK.

12:21.809 --> 12:23.343
TURN BACK.

12:23.410 --> 12:24.812
[WIND WHOOSHES]

12:26.947 --> 12:28.615
SO, WAS THAT
A REAL VISION

12:28.681 --> 12:30.117
OR A VISION
VISION?

12:30.183 --> 12:33.020
IT DOESN'T MATTER.
WE CAN'T TURN BACK

12:33.086 --> 12:35.088
IF WE WANT TO GET
TO DAPHNE.

12:37.357 --> 12:40.193
THIS IS GETTING
HARDER AND HARDER.

12:40.260 --> 12:41.795
MAYBE IT HAS
SOMETHING TO DO

12:41.862 --> 12:44.197
WITH THAT SNORING SOUND?

12:44.264 --> 12:46.233
[SNORING]

12:46.299 --> 12:48.601
WELL, MAYBE WE ALL
NEED A REST.

12:48.668 --> 12:50.170
[SCREECHING]
LOOK!

12:53.006 --> 12:54.942
SHAGGY! SCOOBY!

12:55.008 --> 12:56.877
[SCREECHING]
HUH?

12:58.411 --> 13:00.113
UH-OH!
UH-OH!

13:02.249 --> 13:04.117
WHOA!

13:07.554 --> 13:08.956
* LIVING OUT LOUD *

13:09.022 --> 13:10.757
* TEARIN' MY EYES OUT *

13:10.824 --> 13:13.726
* BURNIN' MEMORIES
BURNIN' OUT *

13:13.793 --> 13:17.130
* DRINK ME AWAY
INTO THE NEXT DAY *

