* NO CON-TROL *

14:00.140 --> 14:03.376
* DRINK YOUR CONSCIENCE
TO FEEL YOUR SOUL *

14:03.443 --> 14:06.079
[SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

14:07.114 --> 14:08.882
EVERYONE SAFE
AND SOUND?

14:08.949 --> 14:11.284
SOUND, MAYBE,
BUT NOT SAFE!

14:11.351 --> 14:13.020
[SCREECHING]

14:14.721 --> 14:16.156
AAH!

14:18.591 --> 14:20.093
[SCREECHING]

14:22.062 --> 14:24.197
[SCREECHING RECEDES]

14:34.307 --> 14:35.442
WE MADE IT.

14:35.508 --> 14:36.977
NOW,
WHERE DO YOU THINK
WE'LL FIND DAPHNE?

14:37.044 --> 14:39.913
MAYBE TRAPPED IN SOME
GIANT BIRD'S NEST.

14:39.980 --> 14:42.182
THAT'S NO BIRD'S NEST.

14:46.053 --> 14:47.454
[STATIC CRACKLING]

14:57.464 --> 15:00.667
WHAT THE HECK
IS GOING ON UP HERE?!

15:09.176 --> 15:11.979
DAPHNE MUST BE
UP HERE SOMEWHERE.

15:17.517 --> 15:19.919
[RUSTLING]

15:19.987 --> 15:22.022
[WHIMPERING] I THINK
THERE'S SOMETHING

15:22.089 --> 15:24.224
UP IN THAT TREE.

15:24.958 --> 15:26.026
CHIRP.

15:26.093 --> 15:27.260
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'
UP HERE?

15:27.327 --> 15:28.861
I'M FINALLY GOING
TO SEE IT.

15:28.928 --> 15:30.163
OH, CHIRP,
CHIRP, CHIRP!

15:30.230 --> 15:32.332
DO YOU KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON UP HERE?

15:32.399 --> 15:33.500
WHO CARES?

15:33.566 --> 15:35.068
WHAT'S IMPORTANT IS
THE SHAME AND DISGRACE

15:35.135 --> 15:36.836
OF NOT SEEING
THAT BIG BIRDY.

15:36.903 --> 15:40.073
I PLAN TO LURE IT
WITH THIS MATING CALL.

15:40.140 --> 15:41.708
NO!
NO!
STOP!

15:41.774 --> 15:43.376
[BIRD WHISTLE SCREECHES]

15:43.443 --> 15:45.178
[SIRENS]

15:45.245 --> 15:47.647
Man on P.A.:
TRESPASSERS HAVE
BREACHED THE PERIMETER!

15:47.714 --> 15:49.382
[ALL GASP]

15:50.550 --> 15:51.584
AAH!

15:56.723 --> 15:58.291
WHOA. WHOA!

15:58.358 --> 16:00.593
WHOA!
AAAHH!
WHOA!

16:00.660 --> 16:01.628
[CRASH]

16:04.397 --> 16:05.565
DAPHNE!

16:05.632 --> 16:07.900
OH, I NEVER THOUGHT
YOU'D FIND ME
UP HERE.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.269
THIS IS
LEON STRONGFEATHER,

16:09.336 --> 16:11.138
THE MISSING EXPLORER
THAT JIMMY TOLD US
ABOUT.

16:11.204 --> 16:12.405
CAN YOU GET US OUT?

16:14.374 --> 16:17.144
WHO ARE THOSE PEOPLE
IN THE SCARY UNIFORMS?

16:17.210 --> 16:19.179
SOME SORT OF
SECRET ORGANIZATION.

16:19.246 --> 16:21.281
I OVERHEARD THEM
TALKING ABOUT
A METEOR SHOWER

16:21.348 --> 16:23.650
THAT COULD HAVE
BROUGHT OTHERWORLDLY
LIFE FORMS.

16:23.716 --> 16:24.817
Shaggy: ZOINKS!

16:24.884 --> 16:26.286
THAT DOES SOUND
PRETTY WEIRD.

16:26.353 --> 16:28.488
NO, I MEAN
THAT ZOINKS!

16:28.555 --> 16:30.723
[SCREECHING]

16:30.790 --> 16:31.991
AAH!
AAH!

16:32.059 --> 16:33.626
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK
FOR YOU, DAPHNE.

16:33.693 --> 16:35.095
RIGHT NOW
WE'VE GOT TO...

16:35.162 --> 16:37.330
RUN FOR OUR LIVES!

16:41.868 --> 16:43.603
[SCREECHING]

16:44.904 --> 16:46.339
THERE MUST BE
SOME CONNECTION

16:46.406 --> 16:49.309
BETWEEN THAT WAKUMI
AND THE SECRET
ACTIVITY UP HERE.

16:49.376 --> 16:51.911
THE ONLY WAY WE'RE GONNA
GET DAPHNE OFF THIS MOUNTAIN

16:51.978 --> 16:53.313
IS IF WE COULD FLY.

16:53.380 --> 16:55.014
I'M WAY AHEAD
OF YOU, SHAGGY.

16:55.082 --> 16:58.085
SOME FALLEN TREE LIMBS,
A FEW TENT TARPS,

16:58.151 --> 17:00.153
A WAD OF GUM
PEELED OFF MY SHOE,

17:00.220 --> 17:02.689
AND VOILA--
A HANG GLIDER FOR 5.

17:02.755 --> 17:04.424
HUH?

17:10.163 --> 17:12.232
SO, WE'RE SUPPOSED
TO GET ON SOMETHING

17:12.299 --> 17:13.600
THAT WAS JUST
THROWN TOGETHER

17:13.666 --> 17:15.034
FROM STUFF IN THE WOODS

17:15.102 --> 17:17.070
AND JUMP IT OVER
THAT VERY HIGH CLIFF,

17:17.137 --> 17:19.939
JUST ON PURE FAITH
IN FRED?
RIGHT.

17:20.006 --> 17:22.742
CAN I HAVE A SECOND
TO THINK AB--AAH!

17:24.444 --> 17:25.778
[GULP]

17:28.281 --> 17:29.749
WHOA!
WHOA!
WHOA!

17:29.816 --> 17:31.751
WHOO!
WHOO!

17:43.029 --> 17:45.398
EVERYBODY, LEAN
TO THE LEFT.

17:46.166 --> 17:47.767
[SCREECHING]

17:47.834 --> 17:48.901
THE WAKUMI!

17:48.968 --> 17:50.770
[SCREECHING]

17:57.477 --> 17:58.645
HOLD TIGHT!

18:03.583 --> 18:06.085
WHOA!
WHOA!

18:06.153 --> 18:07.086
RHOAH!

18:07.154 --> 18:09.021
SCOOBY!
SCOOBY!

18:09.088 --> 18:10.457
[SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

18:12.125 --> 18:13.826
[SCREECHING]

18:23.270 --> 18:25.238
OOH!
OW!
OH!

18:25.305 --> 18:27.374
A PERFECT
3-POINT LANDING.

18:27.440 --> 18:30.543
TOO BAD THIS THING
HAS 5 LANDING POINTS.

18:36.416 --> 18:38.451
IT'S JUST
A GREAT BIG GLIDER.

18:40.220 --> 18:42.489
OXYGEN TANKS, LIKE
THE ONE I FOUND.

18:42.555 --> 18:43.956
THEY MUST BE
FOR BREATHING

18:44.023 --> 18:45.325
IN THE HIGH
ALTITUDES.

18:45.392 --> 18:47.827
TIME TO REVEAL OUR
FINE-FEATHERED FANATIC.

18:48.961 --> 18:51.698
IT'S...

18:51.764 --> 18:53.666
All: NOBODY WE KNOW?

18:58.205 --> 19:00.207
YOU'RE THAT
MYSTICAL SHAMAN.

19:00.273 --> 19:02.609
ACTUALLY,
COLONEL HENRY THORWALL,

19:02.675 --> 19:04.511
COMMANDER OF
THE RESEARCH SITE.

19:04.577 --> 19:06.479
LIKE, WERE YOU
REALLY CHECKING OUT

19:06.546 --> 19:08.681
OUTER-SPACE
LIFE FORMS
ON THAT METEOR?

19:08.748 --> 19:10.149
MY SCIENTISTS
MAY HAVE DISCOVERED

19:10.217 --> 19:11.951
AN EXTRATERRESTRIAL
BREAKTHROUGH.

19:12.018 --> 19:13.353
IT'S BEEN KEPT
TOP SECRET

19:13.420 --> 19:15.222
FROM EVEN
THE U.S. GOVERNMENT.

19:15.288 --> 19:16.889
SO WHY ARE YOU
TELLING US?

19:16.956 --> 19:18.291
NOBODY'S
GONNA BELIEVE

19:18.358 --> 19:20.159
A BUNCH
OF MEDDLING KIDS.

19:20.227 --> 19:21.794
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

19:21.861 --> 19:25.732
SO THE WAKUMI IS NOT
FROM THE ANASAZI CAVE LEGENDS.

19:25.798 --> 19:28.368
HE MADE IT UP
TO SCARE PEOPLE AWAY
FROM THE MOUNTAIN.

19:28.435 --> 19:29.969
AND IF ANYBODY
GOT TOO CLOSE,

19:30.036 --> 19:33.105
HE CARRIED YOU AWAY
TO THAT BIG, BAD
BIRD COOP.

19:33.172 --> 19:35.041
WELL, NOW WE'RE
CARRYING HIM AWAY

19:35.107 --> 19:37.244
TO THE AUTHORITIES
BELOW.

19:42.549 --> 19:46.286
OH, I'LL NEVER CHECK
THAT BIG WAKUMI
OFF MY CARD!

19:46.353 --> 19:49.256
I WON'T BE ABLE
TO HOLD MY HEAD UP
AGAIN!

19:49.322 --> 19:51.791
THEN HOLD THIS UP.
[GASPS]

19:51.858 --> 19:54.461
CHIRP! CHIRP!
CHIRP!

19:54.527 --> 19:56.596
LIKE, WELCOME BACK
SAFE AND SOUND.

19:56.663 --> 19:59.065
I MADE THESE
DREAMCATCHERS
FOR YOU GUYS

19:59.131 --> 20:00.800
SO YOU CAN BLISS OUT

20:00.867 --> 20:02.435
ON YOUR
SWEETEST DREAMS.

20:02.502 --> 20:05.438
AND FROM SHOOBY,
A SPECIAL FAREWELL
TREAT.

20:05.505 --> 20:08.007
Shaggy: WOW!
SHOOBY SNAX!

20:08.074 --> 20:11.244
LIKE, I JUST WISH
I STILL HAD MY
SCULPTURE OF SCOOB

20:11.311 --> 20:12.912
FOR THE EXHIBIT
TOMORROW.

20:12.979 --> 20:14.747
LIKE, NO PROBLEM.

20:14.814 --> 20:16.215
THINK BACK, MAN,

20:16.283 --> 20:18.951
TO OUR DAYS
IN THE SANDBOX?

20:22.355 --> 20:26.459
EVERYONE AT THIS EXHIBIT
SURE LIKES MY LIFE-LIKE
STATUE OF SCOOB.

20:28.495 --> 20:31.764
SCOOBY-DOOBY-DOO!
